<objective>
Turn the thin `spectra_metadata.parquet` (currently a 3-field `spectrum` struct: index/id/time) into the
full packed-parallel table set, and populate the `mzpeak_index.json` `metadata{}` block plus the Parquet
footer KV. This clears the last expected `mzpeak-validate` error (`required facet 'scan' absent`) without
introducing a new one (cv_list must appear the moment CV-named columns do).

Purpose: META-01..05 + IDX-01..04 — emit rich `spectrum`, the required `scan` facet, and the MSn-only
`precursor`/`selected_ion` facets as four co-resident independent tables linked by `source_index`, with
all CV terms as CURIE-named columns; emit the file-level metadata (instrument configurations, software,
data processing, file description, cv_list) into both the index and the footer.

Output: extended `MzPeakParquet` (list-of-struct write path), rewritten `BuildMetadataFacet` + index/
footer assembly in `MzPeakSpectrumWriter`, and NUnit locks. `mzpeak-validate small.mzpeak` shows the
`scan`-facet error GONE and cv_list present.
</objective>

