<interfaces>
<!-- Contracts the executor uses directly. Do NOT re-derive Thermo decoding. -->

Existing MzPeakParquet (extend, don't fork):
- `struct MzPeakParam { long? Integer; double? Float; string String; bool? Boolean; string Accession; string Name; string Unit; }`
- `StructField BuildParamField(string name)` — builds `name: struct<value:struct<integer,float,string,boolean>, accession, name, unit>` (PARAM shape, all leaves nullable).
- `string CvColumn(string accession, string label, string unitAccession = null)` — `"MS:1000016","scan_start_time","UO:0000031"` -> `MS_1000016_scan_start_time_unit_UO_0000031`. Label MUST already be snake_case. Omit unit -> no `_unit_` suffix (use this for `isolation_window_target_mz` which has NO unit suffix in the reference).
- `DataColumn Column(DataField field, Array defined, int[] defLevels, int[] repLevels)`
- `Task WriteAsync(Stream, ParquetSchema, IReadOnlyDictionary<string,string> customMetadata, IDictionary<DataField,(Array defined,int[] defLevels,int[] repLevels)> columns)` — writes Zstd, one row group, iterates `schema.GetDataFields()`, looks columns up by DataField identity (NOT path string).

Existing MzPeakSpectrumWriter helpers (Phase 1/2):
- `static (double[] mz, float[] intensity) OrderedPairs(double[] masses, double[] intensities)` (public).
- `WriteFacet(ParquetSchema, meta, cols)`, `AddStored(zip, name, bytes)`, `Leaf(schema, path)` (path is slash-separated, e.g. `"spectrum/index"`).
- `BuildIndex(bool hasPeaks)` currently emits `{version, files[], metadata:{version}}` via Newtonsoft JObject/JArray, BOM-free UTF8.
- Phase-2 loop already iterates `[firstScanNumber,lastScanNumber]`, gates on `(int)scanFilter.MSOrder` vs `ParseInput.MaxLevel`/`MsLevel`, assigns dense 0-based `ulong ordinal`, and builds `metaIndex/metaId/metaTime`. Phase 3 widens this loop's per-ordinal capture.

Base SpectrumWriter (available to MzPeakSpectrumWriter):
- `static double CalculateSelectedIonMz(IReaction reaction, double? monoisotopicMz, double? isolationWidth)`
- `static IReaction GetReaction(IScanEvent scanEvent, int scanNumber)`
- `protected static double CalculatePrecursorPeakIntensity(IRawDataPlus rawFile, int precursorScanNumber, double precursorMass, double? isolationWidth, bool centroid)` — confirm exact signature in SpectrumWriter.cs before calling.

OntologyMapping (public static — reuse, do not hand-roll CV dicts):
- `Dictionary<MassAnalyzerType,CVParamType> MassAnalyzerTypes` (FTMS->MS:1000079, ITMS->MS:1000264, ...)
- `Dictionary<IonizationModeType,CVParamType> IonizationTypes` (ESI->MS:1000073)
- `Dictionary<ActivationType,CVParamType> DissociationTypes` (CID->MS:1000133, HCD->MS:1000422, ...)
- `CVParamType GetInstrumentModel(string instrumentName)`; `void UpdateFTMSDefinition(string instrumentName)`; `List<CVParamType> GetDetectors(string instrumentAccession)`
- `CVParamType` fields: `accession`, `name`, `value`, `cvRef`, `unitAccession`, `unitName`.

ScanTrailer: `new ScanTrailer(raw.GetTrailerExtraInformation(scanNumber))`; `.AsDouble("Ion Injection Time (ms):")`, `.AsPositiveInt("Charge State:")`.

Thermo per-scan calls (already used in MzMlSpectrumWriter; reuse the VALUE, not the mzML type):
- `raw.GetFilterForScanNumber(n)` -> IScanFilter: `.MSOrder`, `.Polarity` (PolarityType.Positive/Negative), `.MassAnalyzer` (MassAnalyzerType), `.IonizationMode`.
- `raw.GetScanEventForScanNumber(n)` -> IScanEvent: `.ToString()` = filter_string; `.GetReaction(i)` -> IReaction (`.PrecursorMass`, `.CollisionEnergy`, `.CollisionEnergyValid`, `.ActivationType`, `.IsolationWidth`, `.IsolationWidthOffset`).
- `raw.GetScanStatsForScanNumber(n)` -> ScanStatistics: `.TIC`, `.BasePeakMass`, `.BasePeakIntensity`, `.LowMass`, `.HighMass` (confirm member names against the SDK in repo).
- `raw.RetentionTimeFromScanNumber(n)` -> minutes (emit raw, NO conversion).
- `raw.GetInstrumentData()` -> `.Model`, `.SerialNumber`.
- `Scan.FromFile(raw,n).HasCentroidStream`, `scanEvent.ScanData == ScanDataType.Profile` (Phase-2 representation routing already does this).
</interfaces>
