<task type="auto" tdd="true">
  <name>Task 1: list-of-struct (large_list&lt;struct&gt;) write support in MzPeakParquet + round-trip proof</name>
  <files>ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakParquet.cs, ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakParquetTests.cs</files>
  <behavior>
    - A `parameters` column declared as `large_list&lt;PARAM&gt;` round-trips: writing N rows where row r has L_r PARAM entries (including L_r==0 empty lists and a null list) reads back the exact per-row entry counts and leaf values via pyarrow.
    - A `scan_windows` column declared as `large_list&lt;struct&lt;lower:float, upper:float, parameters:large_list&lt;PARAM&gt;&gt;&gt;` round-trips one window per row with nested empty PARAM lists.
    - Repetition levels and definition levels produced by the helper are accepted by Parquet.Net 5.0.1 WriteColumnAsync and by a pyarrow reader (no schema/level mismatch).
  </behavior>
  <action>
    Extend MzPeakParquet with a list-of-struct emission path. Add a helper (e.g. `ListOfStruct`) that, given a `ListField` whose item is a `StructField`, plus the flattened per-row item rows, produces for each leaf DataField the `(defined, defLevels, repLevels)` triple that Parquet.Net's low-level WriteColumnAsync requires for a repeated nested column. Repetition level 0 marks the first element of a new list (new row), level 1 marks subsequent elements within the same list; definition level encodes list-present / list-empty / leaf-null per Parquet.Net's nested-level model for `ListField(StructField(... nullable leaves ...))`.
    Build the list fields with `new ListField(name, BuildParamField("element"))` for PARAM lists and a `ListField` over a `StructField` for scan_windows. Confirm Parquet.Net's expected item-field name (Parquet.Net uses a conventional list item name such as `element`/`item` — inspect `ListField` to match it; the leaf path keying in WriteAsync is by DataField identity so the exact string only matters for level computation). Keep `WriteAsync` keying columns by DataField identity, unchanged.
    Reuse `BuildParamField` for the PARAM element; do NOT introduce a second PARAM struct definition. Compact code, explicit usings, no comments referencing process/phases.
    In MzPeakParquetTests, add a test that writes a temp `.parquet` via the new path with a known ragged set of PARAM lists (e.g. row0: 2 params, row1: 0 params, row2: 1 param) and a scan_windows list, then shells out to `python3 -c` using pyarrow to read it back and print per-row list lengths + a representative leaf value; assert the printed values match. Mirror any existing pyarrow-invocation pattern already used by Phase-1 tests if present; otherwise invoke `python3` via Process and parse stdout. Skip-with-warning (NUnit `Assert.Ignore`) if `python3`/pyarrow is unavailable so the suite stays green in CI without pyarrow.
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>cd /Users/kohlbach/Claude/mzPeak4TRFR && DOTNET_ROOT_X64=$HOME/.dotnet-x64 ~/.dotnet-x64/dotnet test ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.sln --filter "MzPeakParquetTests" 2>&1 | tail -15</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>The list-of-struct round-trip test passes (or Ignores cleanly if pyarrow absent); pyarrow reads back exact per-row PARAM/scan_windows list lengths and a sample leaf value; no other MzPeakParquetTests regress. The rep-level unknown (RESEARCH Open Q1 / Pitfall 3) is retired before any metadata facet is built on it.</done>
</task>

<task type="auto" tdd="true">
