  <action>
    Widen the existing Phase-2 per-scan loop to capture, per emitted ordinal, the rich spectrum + scan fields using the Thermo calls in the reuse table (RESEARCH Decision 2; do NOT re-decode). Map each column with `MzPeakParquet.CvColumn(accession,label,unit)` per RESEARCH Decision 3 (note: scan_start_time/ion_injection_time/scan window limits/base-peak-intensity/TIC are float32; observed-mz/base-peak-mz are double). Set `id` to the Thermo nativeID via the base `ConstructSpectrumTitle`/equivalent (`controllerType=0 controllerNumber=1 scan=N`) — keep it deterministic. ms_level from `(int)scanFilter.MSOrder`; polarity from `scanFilter.Polarity` (Positive->(sbyte)1, Negative->(sbyte)-1); representation from the actual array continuity already determined by the Phase-2 centroid/profile routing (centroid->MS:1000127, profile->MS:1000128); spectrum_type from ms_level (1->MS:1000579 else MS:1000580). number_of_data_points = the as-acquired point count for that ordinal; number_of_peaks = the centroid peak count for that ordinal (0 when no peaks) — both available from the Phase-2 accumulators. TIC/base-peak/observed-mz from ScanStatistics / the emitted arrays.
    Build the instrument-configuration index map: collect the DISTINCT `scanFilter.MassAnalyzer` values in first-seen order across the run; each distinct analyzer is one config (0-based). `scan.instrument_configuration_ref` = the index of that scan's analyzer in this list (RESEARCH Decision 5; reference order 0=FTMS,1=ITMS). Persist this map for Task 4's instrument_configuration_list.
