<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Thermo RAW -> writer | RAW content is read-only input decoded by the vendor SDK; malformed scans already guarded by the Phase-2 per-scan try/catch + ParseInput.NewError(). |
| writer -> .mzpeak archive | Output is a deterministic local file consumed by the reference reader / validator; no network, no untrusted consumer in this phase. |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-03-01 | Tampering | per-ordinal arrays vs four-table null discipline | mitigate | NUnit locks assert def-level discipline (precursor/selected_ion null on rows >= #MSn) and source_index/precursor_index linkage, preventing silently-misaligned tables. |
| T-03-02 | Information disclosure | source RAW path in file_description.source_files[].location | accept | The location is the user-supplied input path written into the user's own output; no new exposure beyond existing TRFP behavior. |
| T-03-03 | Denial of service | full in-memory accumulation of metadata for large RAW | accept | Inherited Phase-2 v1 limitation (single row group, in-memory); large-RAW streaming is OPT/v2 scope, not regressed here. |
| T-03-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | accept | Phase installs NO external packages (RESEARCH: Package Legitimacy Audit N/A); no new dependency surface. |
</threat_model>

