   125	  <files>ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakParquet.cs, ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakParquetTests.cs</files>
   126	  <behavior>
   127	    - A `parameters` column declared as `large_list&lt;PARAM&gt;` round-trips: writing N rows where row r has L_r PARAM entries (including L_r==0 empty lists and a null list) reads back the exact per-row entry counts and leaf values via pyarrow.
   128	    - A `scan_windows` column declared as `large_list&lt;struct&lt;lower:float, upper:float, parameters:large_list&lt;PARAM&gt;&gt;&gt;` round-trips one window per row with nested empty PARAM lists.
   129	    - Repetition levels and definition levels produced by the helper are accepted by Parquet.Net 5.0.1 WriteColumnAsync and by a pyarrow reader (no schema/level mismatch).
   130	  </behavior>
   131	  <action>
   132	    Extend MzPeakParquet with a list-of-struct emission path. Add a helper (e.g. `ListOfStruct`) that, given a `ListField` whose item is a `StructField`, plus the flattened per-row item rows, produces for each leaf DataField the `(defined, defLevels, repLevels)` triple that Parquet.Net's low-level WriteColumnAsync requires for a repeated nested column. Repetition level 0 marks the first element of a new list (new row), level 1 marks subsequent elements within the same list; definition level encodes list-present / list-empty / leaf-null per Parquet.Net's nested-level model for `ListField(StructField(... nullable leaves ...))`.
   133	    Build the list fields with `new ListField(name, BuildParamField("element"))` for PARAM lists and a `ListField` over a `StructField` for scan_windows. Confirm Parquet.Net's expected item-field name (Parquet.Net uses a conventional list item name such as `element`/`item` — inspect `ListField` to match it; the leaf path keying in WriteAsync is by DataField identity so the exact string only matters for level computation). Keep `WriteAsync` keying columns by DataField identity, unchanged.
