   238	### Decision 4 — `mzpeak_index.json` metadata{} block (exact JSON shapes)
   239	
   240	**Source:** `cat refs/mzPeak/small.unpacked.mzpeak/mzpeak_index.json` + `refs/mzPeak/schema/*.json` + validator `schema/json/*.json`. [VERIFIED]
   241	
   242	**Index top level:** `{ "version": "0.9", "files": [...], "metadata": { ... } }`. The validator index
   243	schema **requires** `files` (each item: name, entity_type∈{spectrum,mass spectrum,chromatogram,wavelength spectrum,image,other}, data_kind∈{metadata,data arrays,peaks,other}) and `metadata` (object, **required `version`**).
   244	
   245	> The reference puts `version` at index top level only; the validator reads `metadata.version`. Phase 1
   246	> already writes `metadata.version` (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:283-286). Keep it. The reference's absence of
   247	> `metadata.version` is exactly why it FAILS `index_schema_valid` (Decision 6).
   248	
   249	**Required keys per sub-schema** (from `refs/mzPeak/schema/` and validator `schema/json/`):
   250	- `instrument_configuration` item requires: `id` (int), `components` (array), `parameters` (array), `software_reference` (string). Each component requires `component_type` ∈ {ionsource,analyzer,detector}, `order` (int), `parameters` (array).
   251	- `data_processing_method`: properties `id`, `methods[]` (each: order, software_reference, parameters) — no top-level `required` declared.
   252	- `software`: properties `id`, `version`, `parameters` — no `required` declared.
   253	- `sample` requires: `id`, `name`, `parameters`.
   254	- `ms_run` requires: `id`, `default_instrument_id` (int), `default_data_processing_id` (string), `default_source_file_id` (string); optional `start_time` (RFC3339), `parameters`.
   255	- `file_description`: `contents[]` (PARAM), `source_files[]` (each requires id, name, location, parameters).
   256	- `cv_list` item requires: **`id`, `version`, `uri`** (full_name optional).
   257	- `param`: requires **`name`**; optional accession (CURIE pattern `\S+:\S+` or null), value, unit.
   258	
