   420	
   421	## Architecture Patterns
   422	
   423	### Data flow
   424	```
   425	RAW scan loop (Phase-2 ordinal i)
   426	  ├─> scanFilter / scanEvent / scanStats / trailer   (already read in Phase 2 loop)
   427	  ├─> SPECTRUM table[i]      <- ms_level, polarity, repr, type, obs-mz, base peak, TIC, ndp/npk
   428	  ├─> SCAN table[i]          <- rt, filter, iit, scan_windows, instrument_config_ref(=analyzer idx)
   429	  └─ if ms_level>=2:
   430	       PRECURSOR table[k]    <- source_index=i, precursor_index=lastMS1ordinal, iso window, activation PARAMs
   431	       SELECTED_ION table[k] <- source_index=i, precursor_index=lastMS1ordinal, mz, charge, intensity
   432	        (k = running MS2 counter)
   433	  └─ track lastMS1ordinal = i  when ms_level==1
   434	
   435	After loop:
   436	  N rows. spectrum/scan def-level=1 for all N; precursor/selected_ion def-level=1 for k<M else 0.
   437	  ParquetSchema(spectrum, scan, precursor, selected_ion) -> WriteFacet
   438	  Footer KV: spectrum_count, run, instrument_configuration_list, software_list,
   439	             data_processing_method_list, file_description, sample_list, scan_settings_list
   440	  Index metadata{}: version, cv_list, + same blocks
   441	```
   442	
   443	### Anti-Patterns to Avoid
   444	- **Row-disjoint structs (CONTEXT.md's stated model):** WRONG. Don't emit a row with only one struct populated. Use four independent right-padded tables.
   445	- **Swapping precursor source_index/precursor_index:** source_index=MS2 ordinal, precursor_index=MS1 parent ordinal.
   446	- **Omitting cv_list:** trips `cv_list_declared` the moment CV columns appear (the reference's own bug).
   447	- **Hand-crafting pwiz-identical instrument terms:** use TRFP's `OntologyMapping`; structural conformance is what matters.
   448	- **Converting RT to seconds:** Thermo RT is already minutes; emit raw with unit UO:0000031.
   449	
   450	## Don't Hand-Roll
   451	
   452	| Problem | Don't Build | Use Instead | Why |
   453	|---------|-------------|-------------|-----|
   454	| Thermo scan/precursor/activation decode | custom filter/reaction parsing | `ConstructScanList` / `ConstructPrecursorList` (MzMlSpectrumWriter) | edge cases (SPS, supplemental activation, isolation offset math) already handled |
   455	| Instrument model → CV | custom dict | `OntologyMapping.GetInstrumentModel/MassAnalyzerTypes/IonizationTypes/GetDetectors` | longest-substring matching + FT definition update already done |
   456	| CV column naming | string concat | `MzPeakParquet.CvColumn` | unit-suffix convention proven |
   457	| PARAM struct | new struct type | `MzPeakParquet.BuildParamField` + `MzPeakParam` | shape matches ground truth |
   458	| last-MS1-parent tracking | scan re-scan | mirror `_precursorScanNumbers[""]` pattern | already the established approach |
   459	
   460	## Runtime State Inventory
   461	
   462	This is a writer/code change phase (extends `MzPeakSpectrumWriter`, no rename/migration). No stored
   463	data, live service config, OS-registered state, secrets, or build artifacts carry phase-specific
   464	identifiers. **None — verified: the only outputs are the `.mzpeak` archive (regenerated per run) and
   465	NUnit tests; no persistent external state.**
   466	
   467	## Common Pitfalls
   468	
   469	### Pitfall 1: Treating the four structs as row-aligned
   470	**What goes wrong:** Writing `precursor[i]` for the spectrum at row i.

