   343	### Decision 5 — OntologyMapping → instrument_configuration reuse
   344	
   345	**Source:** `OntologyMapping.cs` + `MzMlSpectrumWriter.cs:281-307, 755-870`. [VERIFIED: file:line]
   346	
   347	| Need | Reuse | file:line |
   348	|------|-------|-----------|
   349	| instrument model CV from Thermo name | `OntologyMapping.GetInstrumentModel(instrumentData.Model)` (exact + longest-substring match) | OntologyMapping.cs:788; called MzMlSpectrumWriter.cs:292 |
   350	| instrument model string + serial | `_rawFile.GetInstrumentData()` → `.Model`, `.SerialNumber` | MzMlSpectrumWriter.cs:283, 303 |
   351	| analyzer CV per scan | `OntologyMapping.MassAnalyzerTypes[scanFilter.MassAnalyzer]` (FTMS→MS:1000079, ITMS→MS:1000264, TOF→MS:1000084, quad→MS:1000081, ...) | OntologyMapping.cs:15-90; used 860 |
   352	| ionization CV | `OntologyMapping.IonizationTypes[scanFilter.IonizationMode]` (ESI→MS:1000073) | OntologyMapping.cs:95; used 772 |
   353	| detector CV list per instrument | `OntologyMapping.GetDetectors(instrumentModel.accession)` (LTQ FT FT→inductive MS:1000624; IT→electron multiplier MS:1000253) | OntologyMapping.cs:857; used 869 |
   354	| one config per distinct analyzer | loop over scans collecting `_massAnalyzers` (distinct `MassAnalyzerType` → "IC1","IC2",...), build a 3-component config (source order1 / analyzer order2 / detector order3) for each | MzMlSpectrumWriter.cs:755-880 |
   355	| dissociation CV | `OntologyMapping.DissociationTypes[reaction.ActivationType]` | OntologyMapping.cs:220 |
   356	
   357	The reference's two instrument_configurations (FTMS=id0, ion-trap=id1) correspond exactly to the two
   358	distinct `MassAnalyzerType` values TRFP collects for small.RAW. `scan.instrument_configuration_ref`
   359	(uint32) = the 0-based index of that scan's analyzer config. The Phase-3 plan should build the config
   360	list with this loop and map each scan's `scanFilter.MassAnalyzer` to its config index.
